</ul>



<p>They can be customized and modified to fit a variety of workout goals based on fitness level and experience.</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Best Chest And Tricep Workout Women</h2>



<p>The following exercises target and strengthen your chest and triceps for an effective upper-body workout. You can program them as listed or in the order of your preference.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Pullover">Dumbbell Pullover</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-pullover" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell pullover</a> effectively targets the back, triceps, and chest muscles. During the overhead extension movement, it primarily activates the latissimus dorsi. The chest muscles, triceps, and core also engage to support the elbow joint and lower back throughout the movement.</p>



<p>This exercise benefits women by improving upper body development while supporting shoulder and elbow joint stability. It also improves performance in activities that involve throwing or shoulder rotation, such as tennis, powerlifting, and swimming.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Dumbbell Pullover" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/984680529?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Pullover Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Lie flat on a bench with your head near one end and your feet flat on the ground for stability.</li>



<li>Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms pressed inward on the weight plate, and thumbs wrapped around the handle for a secure grip.</li>



<li>Extend your arms straight above your chest, with a slight bend in your elbows.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core while ensuring your back remains flat against the bench.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc-like motion over your head, keeping your arms slightly bent. Lower the weight until your arms are in line with your torso.</li>



<li>Exhale as you reverse the motion, bringing the dumbbell back over your chest.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Choose the correct weight that allows for proper form and technique.</li>



<li>Keep your elbows slightly bent to reduce stress on the joints and focus on engaging your chest and back.</li>



<li>Ensure your back remains flat and in contact with the bench for stability. This will prevent straining your lower back, which can lead to injuries.</li>



<li>Maintain control on the descent phase to engage the target muscles and prevent shoulder strain effectively.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">6â€“8</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8â€“15</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">15â€“20</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3â€“6 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Dumbbell Pullover</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Triceps-Dip">Triceps Dip</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/triceps-dips" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Tricep dips</a> are a popular component of many <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-tricep-workouts" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">tricep workouts</a> as they are versatile. They isolate the triceps as the prime movers. They also work the chest, shoulders, and core, providing stability and support throughout the exercise.</p>



<p>Tricep dips also improve functional strength, as the targeted muscles are all involved in daily tasks like lifting, pulling, and carrying. Requiring only body weight and a sturdy flat surface, it is very beneficial for women.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Triceps Dips" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/964108543?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Triceps Dip Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin by standing between two parallel bars that will be used to hold yourself up.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Grip the bars with palms facing inward to your torso and arms extended. Your feet should be lifted off the ground.</li>



<li>Inhale as you engage your core and lower your upper body until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle.</li>



<li>Exhale as you push back up, fully extending the arms back to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>This can be performed using a bench or chair with a sturdy surface, increasing the versatility of the exercise.</li>



<li>Ensure that your core is engaged throughout the movement.</li>



<li>Use stable and controlled movements and avoid swinging or using momentum through the range of motion.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



