</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Chest Fly Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. Keep your feet firmly planted on the ground.</li>



<li>Extend your arms above your chest with a slight bend in your elbows to protect your joints.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Keep your back against the pad with your head facing forward.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the dumbbells on either side until they are level with your chest. You should feel a stretch across your pectorals (chest muscles).</li>



<li>Exhale and squeeze your chest to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position, focusing on controlled, deliberate movement.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">TipsÂ </h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a slight bend in your elbows. This helps to prevent joint strain from hyperextending your elbows.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Use an appropriate weight that allows you to perform the exercise in the correct form.Â </li>



<li>Engage to maximize the stretch in your chest at the bottom of the movement.</li>



<li>Make sure the bench is set to the optimal angle to target the focus areas of the chest.</li>
</ul>



