<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Push-Up">Push-Up</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Push-ups</a> are a great chest and tricep workout for women. They build upper-body functional strength and improve core stability. Push-ups can easily be modified based on your fitness level and goals, making them effective for any fitness level and goal. Additionally, they require no equipment and can be performed anywhere.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/957562432?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Push-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin lying face down with your hands shoulder-width on the floor, placed beneath your shoulders.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Your legs should be extended behind you, forming a straight line with your body from your head to your feet.</li>



<li>Inhale to engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale to push through your hands and lift your body off the ground. Maintain a neutral spine with your back straight.</li>



<li>Hold at the top for a count and then inhale to lower back down, maintaining control throughout the movement.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core engaged throughout, and avoid letting your hips drop or raise out of alignment.</li>



<li>Try different hand placements to increase the activation of different muscles. A narrower placement increases focus on the triceps and a wider placement increases chest activation.</li>



<li>Use a modified variation (knees on the ground) until you gain strength to maintain proper form and protect the lower back.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



