<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Chest</h2>



<p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538321/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">chest muscles</a> are on the upper frontal region of the torso. They consist of three primary components: the pectoral muscles, intercostal muscles, and diaphragm.Â </p>



<p>These muscles work together to support essential movements, including shoulder flexion and stabilization and internal rotation of the upper arm. They also assist in mobilizing the rib cage during breathing to bring air in and out of the lungs.</p>


