<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Triceps</h2>



<p>The<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK536996/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"> triceps brachii</a> muscle group is located on the posterior side of the upper arm, between your shoulders and forearms. They consist of three heads â€” the triceps long head, triceps medial head, and triceps lateral head.</p>



<p>They primarily function to extend the elbow, making them essential in upper body lifts and functional movements. They also support shoulder and elbow stability in many daily tasks.</p>


